==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tight
<hw>Tight</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Tighter</adjf> <pr>(t⟦imac⟧t"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Tightest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>tight</ets>,
<ets>thiht</ets>; probably of Scand. origin; cf. Icel.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦emac⟧ttr</ets>, Dan. <ets>t⟦ae⟧t</ets>, Sw.
<ets>t⟦aum⟧t</ets>: akin to D. & G. <ets>dicht</ets> thick, tight, and
perhaps to E. <ets>thee</ets> to thrive, or to <ets>thick</ets>. Cf.
<er>Taut</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Firmly held together; compact;
not loose or open; <as>as, <ex>tight</ex> cloth; a <ex>tight</ex>
knot.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Close, so as not to admit the passage of a liquid or
other fluid; not leaky; <as>as, a <ex>tight</ex> ship; a <ex>tight</ex>
cask; a <ex>tight</ex> room</as>; -- often used in this sense as the
second member of a compound; <as>as, water-<ex>tight</ex>;
air-<ex>tight</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fitting close, or too close, to the body; <as>as, a
<ex>tight</ex> coat or other garment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not ragged; whole; neat; tidy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Clad very plain, but clean and <qex>tight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll spin and card, and keep our children <qex>tight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Close; parsimonious; saving; <as>as, a man
<ex>tight</ex> in his dealings</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Not slack or loose; firmly stretched; taut; --
applied to a rope, chain, or the like, extended or stretched
out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Handy; adroit; brisk.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>Somewhat intoxicated; tipsy.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>9.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>Pressing; stringent; not easy;
firmly held; dear; -- said of money or the money market. Cf.
<er>Easy</er>, 7.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tight</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tight
<hw>Tight</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To tighten.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tighten</ent>⟦br⟧
